</p>
<p>What if we want to re-use this class with a different configuration? Or what
if our beta and production setups use different SMTP servers? Right now, both
are impossible!</p>
<h2 id="injecting-configuration">Injecting Configuration <a class="headerlink" href="injection-interfaces#injecting-configuration" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>When we realized that <code>FriendHarvester</code> needed the PDO object, we injected
it via the constructor. The same rule applies to configuration. Add a second
constructor argument, which will be an array of SMTP config and update the
code to use it:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="962b7dfccd">
