<p>Try it out to make sure it still works:</p>
<pre><code class="language-bash"><div class="line">php app.php</div></code></pre>
<p>We would hate for our friends to miss this opportunity!</p>
<p>Once again, this makes the <code>FriendHarvester</code> even more flexible and readable,
and will also make re-using the mailer possible. As a general rule, it's almost
always better to inject a service into another than to create it internally.
When you're in a service, think twice before using the <code>new</code> keyword, unless
you're instantiating a simple object that exists just to hold data as opposed
to doing some job (i.e. a "model object").</p>
<h2 id="type-hinting">Type-Hinting <a class="headerlink" href="injection-interfaces#type-hinting" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>One thing we've neglected to do is type-hint our two constructor arguments.
Let's do it now:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="ecd1bb207e">
